decision_conditions:
The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.


REASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

The development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans and documents hereby approved, including the arboricultural method statement.


REASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved and to safeguard trees of significant amenity value.
subdivision_of_building: The proposal only affects a collapsed section of wall on the park boundary.
description: Replacement of part of boundary wall with fence on Spring Hill boundary near junction with Ashtead Road
